request.description:
This fetches status for **all active** jobs, and returns them all at once. It takes no parameters (except an [API Key](https://github.com/jhuckaby/Cronicle/blob/master/docs/APIReference.md#api-keys) of course). The response format is as follows:

```
{
    "code": 0,
    "jobs": {
        "jk6lmar4c01": {
            ...
        },
        "jk6lmar4d04": {
            ...
        }
    }
}

 ```

This fetches the current application "state", which contains information like the status of the scheduler (enabled or disabled). The API accepts no parameters. Example response:

``` json
{
    "code": 0,
    "state": { "enabled": 1 }
}

 ```
